
[1]public-spirited

   PUBLIC-SPIR'ITED, a. Having or exercising a disposition to advance the
   interest of the community; disposed to make private sacrifices for the
   public good; as public-spirited men.

   1. Dictated by a regard to public good; as a public-spirited project or
   measure.
